  "notes": "PLAN §12 row 18. Spike-gated template shipped as REAL (NOT_ANSWERABLE fallback NOT taken) -- the late-clock PBP data is reliable from 1996-97 onward. Definition (Option B, aligned with Basketball-Reference): the made FG-or-FT that produced the game's final lead change (scoring team tied/trailing immediately before -> leading after), in the last clock_window seconds of Q4/OT. Kobe has 14 such plays under this definition. This corrects the prior FG-only logic, which (a) missed free-throw buzzer-beaters entirely and (b) over-counted insurance FGs scored while the winner was already leading -- 3 of the old 17 were last-3s FGs with the Lakers already up 3-7 (game_ids 0029700135, 0020100259, 0020800405) and are now correctly excluded. team_id 1610612747 = LAL; opponents map to varying franchises (POR=1610612756, MIA=1610612748, etc.). Includes the famous 2000-05-10 WCF Game-7 jumper vs Portland and the 2009-12-04 jumper over Dwyane Wade."
